%26quot%3B%20man%20of%20small%20stature%2C%20Mohammed%20also%20had%20a%20reputation%20for%20being%20short-tempered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20around%2060%20years%20old%2C%20the%20trained%20engineer%20was%20involved%20in%20a%20string%20of%20major%20plots%20against%20the%20United%20States%2C%20where%20he%20attended%20university%20and%20attained%20an%20engineering%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20deadliest%20was%20the%209%2F11%20operation%2C%20which%20saw%20nearly%203%2C000%20people%20killed%20after%20hijacked%20planes%20rammed%20into%20the%20Twin%20Towers%20in%20New%20York%20and%20the%20Pentagon%20in%20Washington%2C%20with%20another%20crashing%20in%20a%20Pennsylvania%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20claims%20to%20have%20helped%20in%20the%201993%20World%20Trade%20Center%20bombing%20that%20killed%20six%20people%20and%20to%20have%20personally%20beheaded%20US%20journalist%20Daniel%20Pearl%20in%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKSM%20was%20born%20in%20the%20mid-1960s%20to%20a%20Pakistani%20family%20living%20in%20Kuwait%2C%20but%20his%20roots%20lie%20in%20Baluchistan%2C%20a%20restive%20Pakistani%20region%20bordering%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20he%20joined%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20an%20anti-Zionist%20activist%20group%2C%20when%20he%20was%2016%2C%20beginning%20a%20life-long%20infatuation%20with%20violent%20jihad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201983%2C%20Mohammed%20moved%20to%20the%20United%20States%20for%20his%20studies%20and%20stayed%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmall%20group%26quot%3B%20of%20Arabs%20from%20Kuwait%2C%20biographer%20Richard%20Miniter%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKSM's%20limited%20and%20negative%20experience%20in%20the%20United%20States%20--%20which%20included%20a%20brief%20jail%20stay%20because%20of%20unpaid%20bills%20--%20almost%20certainly%20helped%20propel%20him%20on%20his%20path%20to%20becoming%20a%20terrorist%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20US%20intelligence%20summary%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201987%2C%20he%20traveled%20to%20Afghanistan%20and%20fought%20alongside%20mujahedeen%20rebels%20against%20the%20Soviet%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20stayed%20in%20Afghanistan%20until%201992%2C%20and%20then%20headed%20to%20Bosnia%20and%20Herzegovina%20to%20fight%20with%20Muslim%20fighters%20against%20the%20Serbs%2C%20according%20to%20the%209%2F11%20Commission%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20not%20until%20a%20botched%201995%20plot%20to%20blow%20up%20US%20airliners%20over%20the%20Pacific%2C%20known%20as%20Operation%20Bojinka%2C%20that%20he%20achieved%20notoriety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20earlier%20helped%20finance%20the%201993%20World%20Trade%20Center%20bombing%20hatched%20by%20his%20nephew%20Ramzi%20Youssef%20that%20killed%20six%20people%20and%20wounded%20more%20than%201%2C000%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammed%20fought%20alongside%20Bin%20Laden%20in%20Afghanistan%20in%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20but%20they%20did%20not%20forge%20a%20close%20relationship%20until%2010%20years%20later%2C%20at%20which%20point%20Mohammed%20began%20plotting%20what%20would%20later%20become%20the%20September%2011%2C%202001%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBin%20Laden%20realized%20that%20this%20difficult%20little%20man%20was%20absolutely%20essential%20for%20turning%20AQ%20into%20the%20kind%20of%20organization%20he%20wanted%2C%26quot%3B%20Miniter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammed%20then%20had%20a%20hand%20in%20nearly%20every%20single%20Al-Qaeda%20plot%20until%20his%20arrest.%20But%20experts%20say%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20that%20one%20man%20alone%20was%20at%20the%20center%20of%20all%20these%20terror%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20obviously%20a%20smart%20guy%2C%20but%20he's%20not%20a%20genius...%20He%20didn't%20do%20the%20impossible%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Terry%20McDermott%2C%20co-author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Hunt%20for%20KSM.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20what%20is%20known%20about%20Mohammed%20comes%20from%20interrogation%20transcripts%20released%20by%20the%20Pentagon.%