eived%20in%20Switzerland%20to%20be%20much%20greater%20than%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20system%20seemed%20broken%2C%20and%20she%20felt%20fortunate%20not%20to%20be%20a%20first-time%20mother.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPerched%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20exam%20table%20at%20my%20doctor's%20office%20in%20a%20Chicago%20suburb%2C%20I%20was%20shivering%20under%20my%20thin%20gown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20you%20have%20any%20questions%20about%20the%20delivery%3F%26quot%3B%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fobgyns-debunk-13-childbirth-myths-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOB-GYN%3C%2Fa%3E%20stepped%20back%20and%20readjusted%20her%20glasses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20paused.%20My%20questions%20were%20not%20about%20the%20mechanics%20of%20delivery%2C%20since%20I%20had%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fswiss-vs-american-parenting-differences-independence-freedom-culture-shock-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egiven%20birth%20once%20before%20in%20Switzerland%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20more%20about%20the%20way%20birth%20was%20handled%20in%20a%20place%20that%20still%20felt%20foreign%20to%20me%20after%20almost%20a%20decade%20away%20%E2%80%94%20my%20own%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20ask%20why%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2017%2F05%2F12%2F528098789%2Fu-s-has-the-worst-rate-of-maternal-deaths-in-the-developed-world%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20has%20the%20highest%20maternal%20death%20rates%20in%20the%20developed%20world%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20wanted%20to%20ask%20if%20the%20birth%20would%20cost%20more%20than%20%243%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20the%20price%20for%20delivery%2C%20and%20a%20five-night%20stay%20in%20a%20Swiss%20hospital%2C%20which%20is%20fully%20covered%20by%20Swiss%20insurance.%20I%20wanted%20to%20ask%20why%20we%20are%20the%20only%20developed%20nation%20in%20the%20world%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaternity-leave-around-the-world-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithout%20paid%20family%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20I%20asked%20something%20simpler.%20Something%20that%20had%20a%20yes%20or%20no%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDoes%20the%20hospital%20have%20birthing%20stools%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20doctor's%20wrinkles%20deepened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20a%20birthing%20stool%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22398c06b3-cba5-41f2-9943-3fae5646391a%5C%22%3EArrival%20at%20the%20delivery%20ward%20in%20the%20US%20vs%20Switzerland%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20no%2C%20the%20suburban%20Chicago%20hospital%20had%20no%20birthing%20stool.%20When%20I%20arrived%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-long-does-labor-last%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efully%20dilated%20and%20ready%20to%20deliver%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20also%20had%20no%20record%20of%20me%20(or%20perhaps%20more%20importantly%2C%20of%20my%20insurance)%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20had%20already%20been%20there%20for%20my%20two%20allotted%20ultrasounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20stood%20there%2C%20wincing%20in%20pain%20while%20they%20messed%20with%20their%20computer%2C%20I%20learned%20my%20first%20lesson%20at%20the%20American%20hospital%3A%20You%20can't%20push%20unless%20they%20can%20confirm%20you%20can%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20%26quot%3Bwelcome%26quot%3B%20was%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20my%20arrival%20at%20the%20Swiss%20hospital%2C%20where%20nurses%20met%20me%20at%20the%20door%20with%20a%20wheelchair%20and%20whisked%20me%20away%20to%20a%20birthing%20room%2C%20with%20no%20bureaucracy%20to%20hold%20my%20labor%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20finally%20deemed%20worthy%20of%20a%20room%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-wealthy-investors-got-rich-looting-needy-hospitals-healthcare-system-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20hospital%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20shown%20to%20a%20bed.%20I%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20on%20a%20bed.%20I%20knew%20from%20birthing%20my%20first%20child%20that%20lying%20on%20a%20bed%20was%20the%20most%20uncomfortable%20position%20of%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20because%20the%20Swiss%20and%20German%20midwives%20who%20had%20attended%20the%20birth%20of%20my%20first%20child%20had%20prompted%20me%20to%20try%20almost%20every%20position%20and%20option%20they%20knew%20of%20to%20find%20what%20would%20make%20me%20the%20most%20comfortable.%20Yet%20when%20I%20continued%20to%20request%20an%20alternative%20situation%20at%20the%20US%20hospital%2C%20the%20nurse%20gave%20me%20an%20oxygen%20mask%20instead%2C%20perhaps%20to%20keep%20me%20quiet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d561c2ff-0340-4dcb-a498-f80d52f28cba%5C%22%3EI%20felt%20lucky%20not%20to%20be%20a%20first-time%20mom%20in%20America%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20major%20difference%20was%20the%20overall%20level%20of%20care%2C%20both%20in%20the%20hospital%20and%20outside%20it.%20In%20Switzerland%2C%20the%20standard%20of%20care%20is%20a%20five-day%20hospital%20stay%20for%20a%20vaginal%20birth%20and%20a%2010-day%20hospital%20stay%20for%20a%20C-section.%20Despite%20having%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnewshour%2Fshow%2Fhow-switzerland-delivered-health-care-for-all-and-kept-its-private-insurance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprivate%20insurer-based%3C%2Fa%3E%20system%20like%20the%20US%2C%20the%20Swiss%20system%20is%20tightly%20regulated%20by%20a%20government%20that%20acknowledges%20that%20there's%20a%20basic%20level%20of%20care%20that%20all%20people%20deserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20the%20belief%20that%20a%20woman%20and%20her%20newborn%20need%20close%20monitoring%20across%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20time%20to%20ensure%20positive%20health%20outcomes%20for%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContrast%20this%20to%20the%20US%2C%20where%20I%20was%20discharged%20after%20less%20than%2040%20hours%2C%20with%20no%20follow-up%20care%20included%20other%20than%20a%20six-week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdifferences-between-giving-birth-in-sweden-and-the-us-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epostpartum%20check-up%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20my%20OB-GYN's%20office.%20If%20I%20had%20been%20a%20first-time%20mother%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20couldn't%20have%20been%20taught%20to%20breastfeed%20right%20at%20the%20hospital%2C%20as%20a%20mother's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-know-about-breastfeeding-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emilk%20doesn't%20come%20in%20for%20three%20or%20five%20days%20after%20birth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20five-day%20hospital%20stay%20in%20Switzerland%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20constantly%20monitoring%20my%20baby%20and%20my%20health%2C%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftricks-to-make-breastfeeding-easier-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaught%20to%20breastfeed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20diaper%2C%20and%20bathe%20my%20baby.%20I%20was%20asked%20if%20I'd%20like%20to%20go%20outside%20for%20a%20walk%20in%20the%20woods.%20I%20was%20also%20given%20a%20candlelight%20dinner%20with%20my%20husband%20within%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20level%20of%20care%20was%20outstanding%2C%20even%20with%20my%20basic%20Swiss%20health%20insurance%20(premium%20%24274%20a%20month)%20and%20even%20at%20a%20public%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20after%20five%20days%2C%20I%20was%20only%20allowed%20to%20be%20discharged%20knowing%20I'd%20be%20under%20the%20continued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fwhat-is-a-midwife%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecare%20of%20a%20midwife%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20came%20to%20my%20own%20home%20to%20check%20on%20me%20and%20the%20baby%20for%20another%2010%20days%20over%20the%20next%20month.%20All%20are%20covered%20completely%20by%20my%20Swiss%20insurance%2C%20with%20no%20surprise%20billing%20included.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222643%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20holding%20baby%20in%20carrier%20with%20Switzerland%20mountains%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66aa18b9aab37011780bea44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221982%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20found%20giving%20birth%20in%20Switzerland%20much%20easier%20than%20back%20home%20in%20Chicago.%3Cp%3EChantal%20Panozzo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20had%20taken%20this%20level%20of%20care%20for%20granted.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20it%20compared%20to%20what%20new%20mothers%20experience%20in%20the%20US.%20But%20now%20I%20know%3A%20No%20time%20to%20heal%20or%20learn%20to%20breastfeed%20in%20a%20hospital%2C%20hardly%20any%20follow-up%20care%20for%20the%20newborn%20or%20herself%2C%20no%20legally%20mandated%20paid%20leave%2C%20and%20stress-inducing%2C%20opaque%20costs%20surrounding%20delivery%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20US%2C%20non-medicated%20birth%20cost%20my%20insurer%20over%20%249%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20three%20times%20the%20Swiss%20price%20for%20much%20less%20care%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20was%20%26quot%3Blucky.%26quot%3B%20The%20average%20US%20birth%20costs%20insurers%20%2418%2C865%2C%20with%20out-of-pocket%20payments%20for%20women%20enrolled%20in%20large%20group%20plans%20totaling%20%242%2C854%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthsystemtracker.org%2Fbrief%2Fhealth-costs-associated-with-pregnancy-childbirth-and-postpartum-care%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeterson-KFF%20Health%20System%20Tracker%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20a%20staggering%20price%20to%20pay%20by%20world%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224a1cc28a-748b-4aa8-abbb-2f483bbccfe6%5C%22%3EThe%20system%20in%20the%20US%20felt%20broken%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20later%2C%20I