kushima%20island.%3Cp%3EElmurod%20Usubaliev%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crew%20decided%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20mission%20before%20two%20more%20warnings%20and%20a%20more%20serious%20alert%20of%20a%20persistent%20chip%20in%20the%20gearbox%20meant%20the%20crew%20had%20to%20land%20%26quot%3Bas%20soon%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%20They%20diverted%20to%20Yakushima%20Island%20in%20Japan%2C%20which%20has%20a%20small%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chips%20were%20actually%20part%20of%20a%20gear%20that%20was%20slowly%20disintegrating%20inside%20the%20gearbox.%20Eventually%2C%20a%20large%20enough%20piece%20of%20the%20gear%20sheared%20off%20and%20severely%20damaged%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20gearbox%2C%20stopping%20the%20left%20proprotor%20from%20spinning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20resulted%20in%20a%20complete%20roll.%20%E2%80%A6%20The%20aircraft%20did%20two%20full%20rolls%20and%20ended%20up%20impacting%20the%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20Lt.%20Gen.%20Michael%20Conley%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Air%20Force%20Special%20Operations%20Command%2C%20told%20reporters%20at%20a%20briefing%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGundam%2022%20crashed%20into%20the%20water%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Yakushima%20as%20the%20crew%20was%20waiting%20to%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20this%20series%20of%20decisions%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20the%20pilots%20%26quot%3Binadequately%20prioritized%20continuing%20the%20mission%20over%20considerations%20related%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20extended%20flight%20without%20redundancy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20phenomenon%20of%20chipping%20in%20the%20aircraft%20gearboxes%20is%20not%20new%20and%2C%20while%20the%20report%20faults%20the%20crew%2C%20Conley%20also%20told%20reporters%20that%20the%20airmen%20didn't%20actually%20violate%20any%20policy%20and%20broadly%20acted%20in%20accordance%20with%20their%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202024%2C%20NBC%20reported%20that%20%26quot%3Bsince%20July%202022%2C%20there%20have%20been%20at%20least%20seven%20instances%20of%20metal%20chips%20found%20in%20the%20%5BOsprey%5D%20gearboxes%2C%20though%20no%20fatalities%20have%20resulted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crash%20report%20also%20notes%20that%20the%20chipping%20problem%20was%20known%20to%20the%20military%20office%20that%20oversees%20the%20Osprey%20and%20that%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Binadequate%20action%26quot%3B%20on%20its%20part%20in%20dealing%20with%20the%20issue%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Bprevented%20comprehensive%20awareness%20of%20%5Bproprotor%20gearbox%5D%20risks%2C%20and%20substantially%20contributed%20to%20the%20mishap.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Debris%20believed%20to%20be%20from%20a%20US%20military%20Osprey%20aircraft%20is%20seen%20in%20waters%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Yakushima%20Island.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ac0ecab4912df3ae1864f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDebris%20believed%20to%20be%20from%20a%20US%20military%20Osprey%20aircraft%20is%20seen%20in%20waters%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Yakushima%20Island.%3Cp%3EJapan%20Coast%20Guard%20via%20AP%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20that%2C%20the%20report%20also%20found%20fault%20with%20the%20crew%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.afsoc.af.mil%2FNews%2FArticle-Display%2FArticle%2F3600634%2Fafsoc-aircraft-mishap-releases%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewhom%20the%20Air%20Force%20previously%20called%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bthe%20best%20of%20us%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bnaturally%20talented%26quot%3B%20pilots%20%E2%80%94%20saying%20that%20they%20had%20%26quot%3Ban%20insufficient%20sense%20of%20urgency%20throughout%20the%20entire%20mishap%20sequence%26quot%3B%20and%2C%20once%20a%20fifth%20warning%20cropped%20up%20and%20the%20pilots%20finally%20decided%20to%20land%2C%20they%20did%20not%20choose%20the%20closest%20airfield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20immediately%20clear%20from%20the%20report%20that%20the%20crew%20had%20any%20other%20indications%20that%20something%20was%20seriously%20wrong%20with%20their%20aircraft%2C%20and%20Conley%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20this%20specific%20part%20has%20failed%20on%20a%20V-22%20of%20any%20any%20type%20in%20almost%20800%2C000%20flight%20hours.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20three-star%20general%20and%20V-22%20pilot%20also%20described%20the%20warnings%20the%20crew%20was%20seeing%20as%20%26quot%3Bkind%20of%20like%20a%20check%20engine%20light%20in%20your%20car%20%E2%80%94%20you%20could%20drive%20your%20car%20for%2010%20years%20and%20not%20get%20any%20or%20you%20could%20drive%20next%20week%20and%20get%20three%20different%20ones%20for%20multiple%20reasons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConley%20told%20reporters%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20chips%20are%20a%20byproduct%20of%20just%20the%20gearboxes%20themselves.%20%E2%80%A6%20It's%20not%20unique%20to%20a%20V-22%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20first%20five%20alarms%20meant%20%26quot%3Bthat%20the%20detector%20had%20detected%20the%20chip%20and%20successfully%20burned%20it%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20confirmed%20that%20the%20pilots%20%26quot%3Bfollowed%20their%20training%20to%20read%20the%20checklists%20and%20to%20look%20for%20secondary%20indications%2C%26quot%3B%20undercutting%20the%20report's%20conclusion%20that%20the%20pilots%20took%20unnecessary%20risks%20with%20%26quot%3Ba%20potentially%20serious%20mechanical%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20he%20said%20the%20crew's%20actions%20contributed%20to%20the%20mishap%2C%20Conley%20told%20reporters%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20nothing%20to%20indicate%20that%20they%20did%20anything%20deliberately%20to%20violate%20any%20policy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20crash%2C%20AFSOC%20protocol%20has%20changed%2C%20and%20crews%20are%20advised%20to%20land%20as%20soon%20as%20practical%20after%20a%20single%20chip%20burn%20and%20%26quot%3Bas%20soon%20as%20possible%26quot%3B%20after%20a%20second%20chip%20burn%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crash%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Yakushima%20Island%2C%20Japan%2C%20on%20Nov.%2029%20marked%20the%20deadliest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fequipment%2Fcv-22-osprey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECV-22%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20incident%20in%20the%20Air%20Force's%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Members%20of%20the%20Japanese%20Navy%20look%20through%20binoculars%20during%20a%20search%20operation%20after%20a%20CV-22%20Osprey%20crash.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ac0b3e393cd3c8629ac6e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22492%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMembers%20of%20the%20Japanese%20Navy%20look%20through%20binoculars%20during%20a%20search%20operation%20after%20the%20CV-22%20Osprey%20crash.%3Cp%3EJapanese%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%2FHandout%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKilled%20in%20the%20crash%20were%20Maj.%20Jeffrey%20T.%20Hoernemann%3B%20Maj.%20Eric%20V.%20Spendlove%3B%20Maj.%20Luke%20A.%20Unrath%3B%20Capt.%20Terrell%20K.%20Brayman%3B%20Tech.%20Sgt.%20Zachary%20E.%20Lavoy%3B%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Jake%20M.%20Turnage%3B%20Senior%20Airman%20Brian%20K.%20Johnson%3B%20and%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Jake%20Galliher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20more%20than%2040%20days%20of%20a%20massive%20search%20effort%2C%20the%20remains%20of%20the%20airmen%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20Spendlove%20%E2%80%94%20were%20recovered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Air%20Force%2C%20alongside%20the%20other%20military%20services%20that%20fly%20the%20Osprey%2C%20grounded%20their%20V-22s%20shortly%20after%20the%20crash.%20Within%20roughly%20four%20months%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20cleared%20the%20services%20to%20fly%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWh