dacious-assassinations-targeting-hezbollah-and-hamas-will-expand-the-war-zone-13188765%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Alarming%20Rise%20In%20Tiger%20Deaths%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20Reserve%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAlarming%20cases%20of%20tiger%20deaths%20and%20hunting%20incidents%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh's%20Bandhavgarh%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20its%20surrounding%20forest%20divisions%20have%20been%20reported%20by%20a%20top%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20report%20by%20the%20forest%20department%20based%20on%20an%20order%20by%20in-charge%20Principal%20Conservator%20of%20Forests%20Shubh%20Ranjan%20Sen%20in%20March%20this%20year%20-%20accessed%20by%20NDTV%20now%20-%20sheds%20light%20on%20a%20concerning%20surge%20in%20tiger%20deaths%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20uncovered%20shocking%20details%20of%20negligence%20and%20procedural%20lapses%20in%20handling%20tiger%20cases%2C%20raising%20serious%20concerns%20about%20the%20state%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%20in%20the%20region.%20Known%20as%20the%20'Tiger%20State'%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20is%20home%20to%20some%20of%20the%20highest%20concentrations%20of%20tigers%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20by%20Mr%20Sen%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20report%2C%20had%20highlighted%20severe%20negligence%20in%20handling%20tiger%20cases%2C%20prompting%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20special%20committee%20to%20investigate%20tiger%20deaths%20from%202021%20to%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20members%20of%20the%20three-people%20committee%20to%20look%20into%20tiger%20deaths%20were%20Indian%20Forest%20Service%20officer%20Ritesh%20Sonfia%2C%20Chairman%2C%20Principal%20Officer%20State%20Tiger%20Strike%20Force%3B%20Dr%20Kajal%20Jaiswal%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%2C%20School%20of%20Wildlife%20Forensics%20and%20Health%2C%20Jabalpur%2C%20and%20Archana%20Joshi%2C%20Advocate%20and%20Wildlife%20Officer%2C%20Katni.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bandhavgarh%20Tiger%20Reserve%20covering%201%2C536.93%20sqkm%20is%20known%20for%20its%20high%20tiger%20density%20and%20diverse%20wildlife%2C%20including%20spotted%20deer%2C%20sambar%2C%20and%20leopards.%20The%20reserve's%20staff%20includes%20a%20field%20director%2C%20a%20deputy%20director%2C%20three%20assistant%20directors%2C%20a%20wildlife%20medical%20officer%2C%2011%20forest%20range%20officers%2C%20a%20field%20biologist%2C%2013%20assistant%20forest%20range%20officers%2C%2028%20forest%20guards%2C%20130%20foresters%2C%20a%20drone%20operator%2C%20128%20permanent%20staff%2C%20and%20605%20temporary%20or%20contractual%20rangers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20identified%20major%20causes%20of%20tiger%20deaths%20over%20the%20past%20three%20years%2C%20including%20electrocution%2C%20conflict%2C%20disease%2C%20old%20age%2C%20organ%20capture%2C%20poisoning%2C%20road%20accidents%2C%20and%20uncertain%20causes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reserve%20reported%20these%20details%20-%2012%20tigers%20died%20in%202021%2C%20nine%20in%202022%20and%2013%20in%202023.%20The%20highest%20mortality%20was%20seen%20in%20the%20Manpur%20buffer%20zone%2C%20followed%20by%20Tal%2C%20Magadhi%2C%20and%20Khitauli%20core%20areas.%20There%20was%20an%20overall%20increase%20in%20mortality%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20uncovered%20shocking%20details%20of%20negligence%20and%20procedural%20lapses%2C%20as%20videography%20of%20postmortems%20was%20not%20conducted%20in%20all%20cases.%20The%20policy%20of%20record%20(POR)%20was%20not%20maintained%20in%20most%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20an%20absence%20of%20prescribed%20veterinarians%20for%20postmortems%2C%20and%20most%20parameters%20were%20not%20followed.%20Efforts%20to%20protect%20crime%20scenes%20were%20inadequate%2C%20and%20dog%20squads%20or%20metal%20detectors%20were%20not%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESample%20collection%20and%20sealing%20were%20poorly%20handled%2C%20affecting%20the%20chain%20of%20custody%20during%20court%20cases.%20Case%20diaries%20or%20documentation%20were%20often%20not%20prepared.%20The%20final%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20(NTCA)%20reports%20were%20not%20submitted%20in%20several%20cases%20by%20both%20Bandhavgarh%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20Shahdol%20Forest%20Range%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20cases%20of%20tiger%20deaths%20were%20superficially%20classified%20as%20infighting%20without%20a%20thorough%20investigation.%20Postmortem%20reports%20often%20lacked%20signatures%20from%20the%20veterinary%20officers%20concerned%2C%20and%20in%20some%20instances%2C%20no%20wildlife%20medical%20officer%20was%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETiger%20population%20in%20the%20Bandhavgarh%20reserve%20increased%20from%2063%20in%202014%20to%20165%20in%202022.%20However%2C%20this%20increase%20has%20been%20accompanied%20by%20a%20concerning%20rise%20in%20tiger%20deaths.%20The%20report%20highlighted%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20developmental%20activities%20that%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20conflicts%20and%20fatalities%20among%20tigers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20the%20increased%20tiger%20population%20forces%20young%20and%20old%20tigers%20to%20move%20out%20of%20core%20areas%20into%20human-populated%20regions%2C%20where%20they%20prey%20on%20livestock.%20This%20has%20escalated%20human-tiger%20conflict%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDevelopmental%20activities%20such%20as%20road%20construction%2C%20building%20projects%2C%20and%20resorts%20in%20and%20around%20Bandhavgarh%20Tiger%20Reserve%20are%20reducing%20tiger%20habitats.%20This%20habitat%20loss%20is%20contributing%20to%20increased%20territorial%20conflicts%20and%20poaching%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722524100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fcft69qf_bandhavgarh-tiger-reserve_625x300_01_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Falarming-rise-in-tiger-deaths-in-madhya-pradesh-reserve-report-6241674%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Alarming%20cases%20of%20tiger%20deaths%20and%20hunting%20incidents%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh's%20Bandhavgarh%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20its%20surrounding%20forest%20divisions%20have%20been%20reported%20by%20a%20top%20official.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Falarming-rise-in-tiger-deaths-in-madhya-pradesh-reserve-report-6241674%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Falarming-rise-in-tiger-deaths-in-madhya-pradesh-reserve-report-6241674%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Falarming-rise-in-tiger-deaths-in-madhya-pradesh-reserve-report-6241674%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20To%20Start%20Cashless%20Treatment%20Scheme%20For%20Road%20Crash%20Victims%3A%20Minister%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20formulated%20a%20scheme%20to%20provide%20cashless%20treatment%20to%20victims%20of%20road%20accidents%20caused%20by%20the%20use%20of%20motor%20vehicle%20and%20initiated%20implementation%20on%20a%20pilot%20basis%20in%20Chandigarh%20and%20Assam%2C%20Parliament%20was%20informed%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20written%20reply%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Union%20Minister%20Nitin%20Gadkari%20said%20under%20the%20scheme%2C%20the%20eligible%20victims%20are%20administered%20health%20benefit%20packages%20relating%20to%20trauma%20and%20polytrauma%20care%20at%20empanelled%20hospitals%20under%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20Pradhan%20Mantri-Jan%20Arogya%20Yojana%20(ABPM-JAY)%2C%20up%20to%20a%20maximum%20of%20Rs%201.5%20lakh%20for%20a%20maximum%20period%20of%20seven%20days%20from%20the%20date%20of%20accident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ministry%20has%20formulated%20a%20scheme%20and%20initiated%20implementation%20on%20a%20pilot%20basis%20in%20Chandigarh%20and%20Assam%20to%20provide%20cashless%20treatment%20to%20victims%20of%20road%20accidents%20caused%20by%20use%20of%20motor%20vehicle%2C%20on%20any%20